CAR TALK APR-19-2014 SAT




Our Show > #1416: I Dream of Fairlanes




#1416: I Dream of Fairlanes


Original Air Date: 04.17.2014
 



Description...



This week on Car Talk, 


   the Auto-Psychiatry booth is open, as Dennis tries to figure out why
          he dreamed about being offered a 1966 Ford Fairlane.
              Is a Fairlane memory buried in his past, 
                  or to paraphrase Dr. Freud, is a heap just a heap?


   Meanwhile, over in the Auto-Relational Department,
           Donna treated herself to a spiffy Mazda Miata,
              but can't get her husband to relinquish the steering wheel.

   Also, Tamson's mechanic may be using the "slow milking" approach
        to diagnosing her Beetle's noise;

   Ray has a few final words on Tommy's Dart; 
      
      and does Dave need driving lessons or relaxation therapy
           to prepare for a Summer trip through Ireland with five women?

     
           All this and more, this week on Car Talk.
